PART: Budget Tracker
NAME: Budget Tracker
STATUS: draft

DATA: Budget Categories
MARKER: budget_categories
INTENT: holds all budget categories and their balances
TAGS: #list
---
The app holds a list of budget categories. Each category has a name, a current balance, and a monthly limit.

STRUCTURE: Dashboard Screen
MARKER: dashboard_screen
INTENT: the main screen showing budget categories and totals
---
The screen has a header with the app name, a section for each budget category with its balance and limit, and a summary of total income and expenses at the bottom.

WHEN: Add Category
MARKER: add_category
INTENT: user adds a new budget category
TAGS: #form, #list, #user
---
When the user taps the "Add Category" button, a form appears. The user fills in the category name and limit. The new category appears in the list with a zero balance.

WHEN: Update Category Balance
MARKER: update_category_balance
INTENT: user updates a category's balance
TAGS: #card, #form, #time, #user
---
When the user taps the "Edit" button on a category card, a form appears. The user updates the balance and confirms. The category's balance updates in real-time on the card.

ASSERT: Category Limits
MARKER: category_limits
INTENT: ensure categories do not exceed their limits
---
A category's balance cannot exceed its monthly limit. If a category's balance reaches its limit, no further expenses can be added to that category.

SURFACE: Error Messages
MARKER: error_messages
INTENT: error messages displayed to the user
TAGS: #error, #user
---
The error messages read "Category limit exceeded" when a user tries to add more to a full category. The add button is labeled "New Category" and the edit button is labeled "Edit Category".